it.polimi.automata.io.iba

Class IBAReader<LABEL extends Label,LABELFACTORY extends LabelFactory<LABEL>,STATE extends State,STATEFACTORY extends StateFactory<STATE>,TRANSITION extends Transition<LABEL>,TRANSITIONFACTORY extends TransitionFactory<LABEL,TRANSITION>,AUTOMATONFACTORY extends IBAFactory<LABEL,STATE,TRANSITION>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.automata.io.iba.IBAReader<LABEL,LABELFACTORY,STATE,STATEFACTORY,TRANSITION,TRANSITIONFACTORY,AUTOMATONFACTORY>
  • Type Parameters:
    LABEL - is the type of the Label which is applied to the transitions of the Incomplete Buchi Automaton which must implement the interface Label
    LABELFACTORY - is the factory which allows to create the labels of the transitions. It must implement the interface LabelFactory
    STATE - is the type of the State of the Incomplete Buchi Automaton. It must extend the interface State
    STATEFACTORY - is the factory which is used to create the states of the Incomplete Buchi Automaton. it must implement the interface StateFactory
    TRANSITION - is the type of the transitions of the automaton. It must implement the interface Transition
    TRANSITIONFACTORY - is the factory which allows to create the transitions. It must implement the interface TransitionFactory
    AUTOMATON - is the type of the automaton. It must extend the interface BA
    AUTOMATONFACTORY - is the factory which is able to create a new empty Incomplete Buchi Automaton. It must implement the interface BAFactory

    public class IBAReader<LABEL extends Label,LABELFACTORY extends LabelFactory<LABEL>,STATE extends State,STATEFACTORY extends StateFactory<STATE>,TRANSITION extends Transition<LABEL>,TRANSITIONFACTORY extends TransitionFactory<LABEL,TRANSITION>,AUTOMATONFACTORY extends IBAFactory<LABEL,STATE,TRANSITION>>

        creates a new Buchi automaton reader which can be used to read a Buchi automaton through the method
        Parameters:
        labelFactory - is the factory which allows to create the labels of the transitions
        transitionFactory - is the factory which allows to create the transitions of the Buchi automaton
        stateFactory - is the factory which allows to create the states of the Buchi automaton
        automatonFactory - is the factory which is used to create the Buchi automaton
        fileReader - is the reader from which the Buchi automaton must be loaded
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the labelFactory, transitionFactory, stateFactory, automatonFactory or the fileReader is null
